The paper deals with pattern mining, which is a subfield of exploratory data analysis. The focus is on discovering and ranking item sets efficiently from real-valued data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). However, given the emphasis on data analysis and mining, cs.DB and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the computation of support and normalizations, which further supports the relevance of cs.DB and cs.LG. The other categories are less likely but still possible, as they also deal with data analysis and machine learning.
